Privacy Policy
Introduction
Welcome to Precise Planning, owned and operated by Precise Planning Group Limited. ("we," "us," or "our"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and securing your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you use our website and finance trading application (collectively referred to as "Services").
Information We Collect
1. Personal Information:
We may collect personal information such as your name, email address, postal address, phone number, date of birth, government-issued identification, and financial information when you use our Services. We may also collect additional information if you choose to participate in our promotions, surveys, or contests.
2. Financial Data:
To provide financial trading services, we may collect and process information related to your trading activities, including transaction details, account balances, and payment information.
3. Usage Information:
We collect information about your interactions with our Services, including but not limited to your IP address, device information, browser type, and pages visited. We may also collect usage data related to your trading activities, such as trade history and order execution.
4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies:
We use cookies, web beacons, and similar tracking technologies to enhance your experience, analyze usage patterns, and improve our Services. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.
How We Use Your Information
1. Providing and Improving Services:
We use your data to deliver and enhance our Services, customize your experience, and develop new features and offerings.
2. Communication:
We may communicate with you to provide updates, account-related notifications, security alerts, and customer support.
3. Personalization:
We use your information to personalize your experience, including providing tailored content, recommendations, and advertisements.
4. Analysis:
We analyze usage data to understand how our Services are used, improve functionality, and optimize performance.
5. Legal Compliance:
We process your data to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our terms and policies.
Sharing Your Information
1. With Your Consent:
We may share your data when you provide explicit consent for specific purposes.
2. Service Providers:
We engage trusted third-party service providers to assist us in delivering and enhancing our Services. These providers may access and process your data on our behalf.
3. Legal Compliance:
We may disclose information when required by law, government authorities, or to protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property.
4. Business Transfers:
In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your data may be transferred to a new entity as part of the transaction.
Data Security
We prioritize the security of your personal information and employ industry-standard measures to protect it from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. Despite our efforts, no data transmission over the internet is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
Your Choices
1. Access and Updates:
You can review, update, or correct your account information at any time.
2. Marketing Communications:
You can opt-out of receiving promotional communications from us.
3. Cookies:
You can manage cookies and tracking technologies through your browser settings.
4. Account Closure:
You can request the closure of your account by contacting us.
Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may revise this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or to comply with legal requirements. When we make changes, we will update the "Effective Date" at the beginning of this policy. We recommend reviewing this policy periodically.
